import { Grid, IconButton, Typography } from '@material-ui/core';
import React from 'react';

function calc() {
	return (
		<Grid
			item
			container
			className="calc-cont"
			direction="column"
			alignItems="center"
			style={{ background: 'red' }}
		>
			<Grid container xs="10" item>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'green' }}>
					<Grid item xs="3" justify="center" container alignItems="center">
						<Typography variant="h2">7</Typography>
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3" justify="center" container alignItems="center">
						<Typography variant="h2">8</Typography>
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3" justify="center" container alignItems="center">
						<Typography variant="h2">9</Typography>
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3" justify="center" container alignItems="center">
						<Typography variant="h2">\</Typography>
					</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'grey' }}>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						4
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						5
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						6
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						x
					</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'grey' }}>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						1
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						2
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						3
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						-
					</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'grey' }}>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						0
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						.
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						=
					</Grid>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						+
					</Grid>
				</Grid>
			</Grid>
		</Grid>
	);
}

export default calc;
